            "text": "<p>Divine Ingredients began, as many good things do, with a simple habit — turning the label over and asking, “but what's really in this?”</p><p>For Preet Bhullar, that question wasn't fleeting curiosity. With a background in microbiology and quality control, she knew exactly what to look for — and more importantly, what didn't belong.</p><p>So, she set a new standard. One rooted in honesty, not marketing.</p><p>Every ingredient is sourced with intention, tested with rigor, and chosen because it earns its place — not because it sounds good on a label. No fillers, no shortcuts — just what nature meant, thoughtfully refined.</p><p>As a women-owned brand, Divine Ingredients carries a quiet confidence — precise, uncompromising, yet deeply personal.</p><p>Because when you know better, you choose better. And once you taste the difference, there's no going back.</p>"
